              "(c) Vanishing line equation [10]": "9/10 — Correctly derives the vanishing line equation A x_v + B y_v + C f = 0 (for Z=f convention) from the orthogonality condition and the vanishing-point parametrization. Collinearity is essentially proven by showing all vanishing points satisfy this linear equation, though the proof is brief and assumes d_Z != 0 without discussing directions parallel to the image plane (points at infinity).",
