              "Extrema+Contrast+Hessian [10]": "8/10 — Covers 3x3x3 (26-neighbor) extrema detection explicitly, includes a contrast threshold with a typical value, and includes the Hessian principal-curvature ratio test formula Tr(H)^2/Det(H) < (r+1)^2/r for edge suppression. Missing details like stating Det(H)>0 and/or the full Taylor expansion-based subpixel refinement, so not fully comprehensive.",
